A few structural notes:

Parts 3–5 form the MVT core (Model-View-Template) and should be read in order — each builds on the previous.
Part 7 (DRF) is increasingly essential since most modern Django projects pair with a JS frontend or mobile app.
Like the Frappe book, every chapter should end with a "Quick Recap" and "Try It Yourself" exercise.
The four projects in Part 10 are deliberately sequenced — each one introduces new complexity and real-world patterns the earlier projects didn't need.
